{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MRsQAUwGy1WCLSFr1eTQSZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 15.2: ESLint no-empty-catch + Boundary Tests\n     2→\n     3→Status: review\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want automated enforcement of error handling and module boundaries,\n     9→So that architectural rules aren't just documented but enforced.\n    10→\n    11→<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→- [x] AC1: Given ESLint runs via `npx eslint src/`, when a `catch {}` block has no body and no `// IGNORE:` comment, then it reports an error <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [x] AC2: Given a boundary test scans `src/`, when it finds `stack === 'nodejs'` (or `python` or `rust`) outside `src/lib/stacks/`, then the test fails <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→- [x] AC3: Given a boundary test scans module imports, when a module imports from another module's internal file (not `index.ts`), then the test fails <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→- [x] AC4: Given all 134 existing bare `catch {}` blocks, when each is audited, then every one either has an `// IGNORE: <reason>` comment, rethrows, or returns `Result.fail()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→- [x] AC5: Given `npm run lint` is added to `package.json`, when executed, then ESLint runs against `src/` and exits 0 on a clean codebase <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→- [x] AC6: Given CI workflow `.github/workflows/release.yml`, when the `test` job runs, then it includes the ESLint lint step <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    21→\n    22→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    23→\n    24→- [x] Task 1: Install and configure ESLint (AC: 1, 5)\n    25→  - [x] 1.1: Install `eslint`, `@eslint/js`, `typescript-eslint` as devDependencies\n    26→  - [x] 1.2: Create `eslint.config.js` (flat config format — ESLint 9+) with TypeScript support\n    27→  - [x] 1.3: Enable `no-empty` rule with `allowEmptyCatch: false`\n    28→  - [x] 1.4: Add `\"lint\": \"eslint src/\"` script to `package.json`\n    29→  - [x] 1.5: Verify `npm run lint` runs and reports empty catch violations\n    30→\n    31→- [x] Task 2: Custom ESLint rule for `// IGNORE:` comment requirement (AC: 1)\n    32→  - [x] 2.1: Create a local ESLint plugin or inline rule in `eslint.config.js` that checks catch blocks: if the catch body is empty OR contains only comments, at least one comment must start with `// IGNORE:`\n    33→  - [x] 2.2: Alternatively, if a custom rule is too complex, enforce via the `no-empty` rule + a BATS or vitest test that greps for `catch {` without `// IGNORE:` in nearby lines\n    34→  - [x] 2.3: Write a vitest test that validates the rule catches violations and allows `// IGNORE:` blocks\n    35→\n    36→- [x] Task 3: Audit and fix all bare `catch {}` blocks (AC: 4)\n    37→  - [x] 3.1: Run `grep -rn 'catch\\s*{' src/ --include='*.ts'` to find all 134 bare catch blocks (excluding `__tests__/`)\n    38→  - [x] 3.2: For each catch block, determine the appropriate action:\n    39→    - If the error is genuinely non-fatal (cleanup, optional read, best-effort operation): add `// IGNORE: <specific reason>`\n    40→    - If the error should be propagated: convert to `Result.fail()` or rethrow\n    41→  - [x] 3.3: Verify `npm run lint` passes after all catch blocks are addressed\n    42→\n    43→- [x] Task 4: Module import boundary test (AC: 3)\n    44→  - [x] 4.1: Create `src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts`\n    45→  - [x] 4.2: Implement test that scans all `.ts` files in `src/` for imports matching `from '...modules/<name>/<internal-file>'` where `<internal-file>` is not `index` or `index.js`\n    46→  - [x] 4.3: Include `src/lib/` domain subdirectories (`coverage/`, `docker/`, `stacks/`, `sync/`, `observability/`) in the boundary check — external consumers must import from their `index.ts`\n    47→  - [x] 4.4: Fix the 3 known violations:\n    48→    - `src/lib/docker/cleanup.ts` imports `../../modules/infra/container-cleanup.js` — change to `../../modules/infra/index.js`\n    49→    - `src/lib/retry-state.ts` imports `../modules/sprint/state.js` — change to `../modules/sprint/index.js`\n    50→    - `src/commands/audit-action.ts` imports `../modules/audit/report.js` — change to `../modules/audit/index.js`\n    51→  - [x] 4.5: Ensure the needed exports are added to the respective `index.ts` barrel files if not already present\n    52→\n    53→- [x] Task 5: Verify stack boundary test coverage (AC: 2)\n    54→  - [x] 5.1: Confirm existing `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/boundary.test.ts` already covers AC2 (it does — already enforces NFR4)\n    55→  - [x] 5.2: Run `npx vitest run src/lib/__tests__/stacks/boundary.test.ts` to verify it passes\n    56→  - [x] 5.3: If needed, extend the existing test to also cover `!==` comparisons (currently only checks `===`)\n    57→\n    58→- [x] Task 6: CI integration (AC: 6)\n    59→  - [x] 6.1: Add `npm run lint` step to `.github/workflows/release.yml` `test` job (after build, before or alongside test steps)\n    60→\n    61→## Dev Notes\n    62→\n    63→### Current State Analysis\n    64→\n    65→- **134 bare `catch {}` blocks** exist in `src/` (excluding tests). Zero have `// IGNORE:` comments. This is the bulk of the work.\n    66→- **ESLint is NOT installed.** The project uses `vitest` for testing, `tsup` for building, and `TypeScript 5.9.3`. No linter is configured.\n    67→- **Existing boundary test** at `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/boundary.test.ts` already covers AC2 (NFR4). It scans for `stack === 'nodejs'/'python'/'rust'` and legacy `stack-detect` imports outside `src/lib/stacks/`. This test passes today.\n    68→- **3 cross-module internal import violations** exist today:\n    69→  - `src/lib/docker/cleanup.ts:9` -> `../../modules/infra/container-cleanup.js`\n    70→  - `src/lib/retry-state.ts:2` -> `../modules/sprint/state.js`\n    71→  - `src/commands/audit-action.ts:11` -> `../modules/audit/report.js`\n    72→- **Module barrel files** (`index.ts`) exist for all 8 modules under `src/modules/`.\n    73→\n    74→### Architecture References\n    75→\n    76→- **Decision 7** (Error Handling): Three strategies — `Result<T>`, typed errors, or explicit `// IGNORE:` with reason. Bare `catch {}` is banned. [Source: architecture-v3.md#Decision 7]\n    77→- **NFR3**: No bare `catch {}` without `// IGNORE:` comment. Enforcement: ESLint rule. [Source: architecture-v3.md#NFRs]\n    78→- **NFR4**: No direct stack conditionals outside `src/lib/stacks/`. Enforcement: Boundary test. [Source: architecture-v3.md#NFRs]\n    79→- **NFR6**: Module imports only through `index.ts`. Enforcement: Boundary test. [Source: architecture-v3.md#NFRs]\n    80→\n    81→### ESLint Configuration Guidance\n    82→\n    83→Use **ESLint 9 flat config** (`eslint.config.js`), not legacy `.eslintrc`. The project is ESM (`\"type\": \"module\"` in `package.json`).\n    84→\n    85→```javascript\n    86→// eslint.config.js\n    87→import eslint from '@eslint/js';\n    88→import tseslint from 'typescript-eslint';\n    89→\n    90→export default tseslint.config(\n    91→  eslint.configs.recommended,\n    92→  ...tseslint.configs.recommended,\n    93→  {\n    94→    rules: {\n    95→      'no-empty': ['error', { allowEmptyCatch: false }],\n    96→      // Disable rules that conflict with existing codebase patterns as needed\n    97→      '@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars': ['error', { argsIgnorePattern: '^_' }],\n    98→    },\n    99→  },\n   100→  {\n   101→    ignores: ['dist/', 'node_modules/', 'coverage/'],\n   102→  },\n   103→);\n   104→```\n   105→\n   106→Start with `no-empty` + `allowEmptyCatch: false`. If a custom `// IGNORE:` check is needed beyond that, implement it as a vitest boundary test (simpler than writing a custom ESLint rule plugin):\n   107→\n   108→```typescript\n   109→// In src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts\n   110→it('all catch blocks have // IGNORE: comment, rethrow, or Result.fail()', () => {\n   111→  // Scan for `catch {` blocks and verify the body isn't bare\n   112→});\n   113→```\n   114→\n   115→### Catch Block Audit Strategy\n   116→\n   117→Most of the 134 bare `catch {}` blocks are in these categories:\n   118→1. **File I/O reads** (scan-cache, state loading) — `// IGNORE: file may not exist, return default`\n   119→2. **Docker operations** (health checks, compose) — `// IGNORE: Docker not available, non-fatal`\n   120→3. **Cleanup operations** — `// IGNORE: cleanup failure is non-fatal`\n   121→4. **Config parsing** — `// IGNORE: malformed config, use defaults`\n   122→5. **stat/readdir calls** — `// IGNORE: directory may not exist`\n   123→\n   124→Do NOT change logic or error handling behavior. Only add `// IGNORE:` comments where the empty catch is intentional. If the catch should propagate, refactor to `Result.fail()`.\n   125→\n   126→### Previous Story Intelligence\n   127→\n   128→Story 15-1 established:\n   129→- `scripts/check-file-sizes.sh` — standalone bash gate script pattern\n   130→- CI integration pattern: add step to `.github/workflows/release.yml` `test` job after `npm run build`\n   131→- `FILE_SIZE_ENFORCEMENT` env var pattern for warn/fail modes\n   132→- BATS tests at `tests/` directory for script validation\n   133→- 325 BATS tests + 143 vitest unit tests currently pass, 96.97% coverage\n   134→\n   135→### Testing Requirements\n   136→\n   137→- All existing tests must continue to pass after changes\n   138→- New boundary test must pass (`npx vitest run src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts`)\n   139→- ESLint must pass on clean codebase (`npm run lint`)\n   140→- Coverage target: maintain current level (do not drop below 90%)\n   141→\n   142→### Project Structure Notes\n   143→\n   144→- ESLint config goes in project root: `eslint.config.js`\n   145→- New boundary test goes in `src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts` (sibling to existing test files in that directory)\n   146→- The stack boundary test already exists at `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/boundary.test.ts` — do NOT duplicate it; just verify it passes\n   147→- No new directories needed\n   148→\n   149→### References\n   150→\n   151→- [Source: architecture-v3.md#Decision 7 — Error Handling]\n   152→- [Source: architecture-v3.md#Decision 8 — Command Structure]\n   153→- [Source: architecture-v3.md#Decision 12 — File Size Enforcement]\n   154→- [Source: architecture-v3.md#NFRs — NFR3, NFR4, NFR6]\n   155→- [Source: epics-architecture-v3.md#Epic 15, Story 15-2]\n   156→- [Source: 15-1-ci-file-size-gate.md — Previous story patterns]\n   157→\n   158→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   159→## Verification Requirements\n   160→\n   161→- [x] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests.proof.md`)\n   162→- [x] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   163→- [x] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   164→\n   165→## Documentation Requirements\n   166→\n   167→- [x] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   168→- [x] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests.md`\n   169→\n   170→## Testing Requirements\n   171→\n   172→- [x] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   173→- [x] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   174→- [x] Coverage target: 100%\n   175→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   176→\n   177→## Dev Agent Record\n   178→\n   179→### Agent Model Used\n   180→\n   181→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   182→\n   183→### Debug Log References\n   184→\n   185→### Completion Notes List\n   186→\n   187→- Task 1: Installed ESLint 10, @eslint/js, typescript-eslint as devDependencies. Created eslint.config.js with flat config format, no-empty rule with allowEmptyCatch: false. Added \"lint\": \"eslint src/\" script to package.json. npm run lint exits 0.\n   188→- Task 2: Implemented catch block enforcement via vitest boundary test in src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts (Task 2.2 approach — simpler than custom ESLint plugin). The test scans all source files for catch blocks and verifies each has an // IGNORE: comment within 3 lines. ESLint no-empty rule catches truly empty catch blocks at lint time.\n   189→- Task 3: Audited and annotated all 134 bare catch blocks across 48 source files with contextual // IGNORE: comments. No logic changes made — only documentation of intent. Also fixed 8 empty catch blocks in verify-env.test.ts that violated the no-empty ESLint rule.\n   190→- Task 4: Created src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts with module import boundary test. Fixed 3 known violations (cleanup.ts, retry-state.ts, audit-action.ts) by changing imports to use barrel files. Also fixed 2 test files (audit.test.ts, onboard.test.ts) that had stale imports from modules/audit/report.js. Updated vi.mock declarations to match new import structure.\n   191→- Task 5: Verified existing stack boundary test at src/lib/__tests__/stacks/boundary.test.ts passes. Already covers AC2 (NFR4) with both === and legacy import checks. No extensions needed.\n   192→- Task 6: Added \"ESLint\" step to .github/workflows/release.yml test job, positioned after build and before unit tests.\n   193→\n   194→### File List\n   195→\n   196→- eslint.config.js (new)\n   197→- package.json (modified — added lint script, eslint devDependencies)\n   198→- src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts (new)\n   199→- src/lib/bmad.ts (modified — IGNORE comments)\n   200→- src/lib/state.ts (modified — IGNORE comments)\n   201→- src/lib/scan-cache.ts (modified — IGNORE comments)\n   202→- src/lib/github.ts (modified — IGNORE comments)\n   203→- src/lib/onboard-checks.ts (modified — IGNORE comments)\n   204→- src/lib/beads.ts (modified — IGNORE comments)\n   205→- src/lib/deps.ts (modified — IGNORE comments)\n   206→- src/lib/verifier-session.ts (modified — IGNORE comments)\n   207→- src/lib/agents/st