int `no-empty` rule covers this case, so risk is mitigated."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aaf78afb2b24413d0 (use SendMessage with to: 'aaf78afb2b24413d0' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 36387\ntool_uses: 33\nduration_ms: 169011</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bab18149-7022-4086-8939-7adb2ed0216c","uuid":"3e2c464c-ab5e-4f06-8f4e-9e4c43c11649","timestamp":"2026-03-25T01:36:12.598Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nIMPORTANT CONTEXT: This story has already been fully developed. All tasks are complete. The story is at \"review\" status. You need to:\n1. Review the code changes for quality issues\n2. Fix any HIGH/MEDIUM issues\n3. Verify tests pass and coverage meets targets\n4. Update the story file status from \"review\" to \"verifying\"\n\nThe key files changed are:\n- eslint.config.js (new) — ESLint flat config\n- src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts (new) — module import boundary tests\n- ~48 source files with // IGNORE: comments added to catch blocks\n- 3 import fixes (cleanup.ts, retry-state.ts, audit-action.ts) to use barrel files\n- .github/workflows/release.yml — added ESLint step\n- package.json — added lint script and eslint devDependencies\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage g