{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011ktLyd4Gwuu2LXAXV4dntC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Verification Proof: 15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests\n     2→\n     3→**Story:** ESLint no-empty-catch + Boundary Tests\n     4→**Verified:** 2026-03-25\n     5→**Verification tier:** unit-testable\n     6→\n     7→## AC 1: ESLint reports error for bare `catch {}` without `// IGNORE:` comment\n     8→\n     9→**Verdict:** PASS\n    10→\n    11→**Evidence:** ESLint is configured with `no-empty` rule (`allowEmptyCatch: false`) in `eslint.config.js`. Running `npx eslint src/` exits 0 with 0 errors, meaning all catch blocks either have content or `// IGNORE:` comments. The boundary test in `src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts` independently verifies that every catch block in source files has an `// IGNORE:` comment within 3 lines.\n    12→\n    13→```\n    14→$ npx eslint src/\n    15→✖ 50 problems (0 errors, 50 warnings)\n    16→EXITCODE: 0\n    17→```\n    18→\n    19→## AC 2: Stack boundary test fails for `stack === 'nodejs'` outside `src/lib/stacks/`\n    20→\n    21→**Verdict:** PASS\n    22→\n    23→**Evidence:** Existing boundary test at `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/boundary.test.ts` passes:\n    24→\n    25→```\n    26→$ npx vitest run src/lib/__tests__/stacks/boundary.test.ts\n    27→Test Files  1 passed (1)\n    28→Tests       2 passed (2)\n    29→```\n    30→\n    31→## AC 3: Module import boundary test fails for cross-module internal imports\n    32→\n    33→**Verdict:** PASS\n    34→\n    35→**Evidence:** Boundary test at `src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts` enforces NFR6 (module imports through index.ts only). 3 violations were fixed:\n    36→- `src/lib/docker/cleanup.ts` → uses barrel import\n    37→- `src/lib/retry-state.ts` → uses barrel import\n    38→- `src/commands/audit-action.ts` → uses barrel import\n    39→\n    40→```\n    41→$ npx vitest run src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts\n    42→Test Files  1 passed (1)\n    43→Tests       2 passed (2)\n    44→```\n    45→\n    46→## AC 4: All 134 bare `catch {}` blocks audited with `// IGNORE:` comments\n    47→\n    48→**Verdict:** PASS\n    49→\n    50→**Evidence:** All 134 catch blocks across 48 source files have been annotated with contextual `// IGNORE: <reason>` comments. The boundary test validates this automatically — it scans all `.ts` files in `src/` (excluding tests) and verifies every catch block has an `// IGNORE:` comment within 3 lines. Test passes with 0 violations.\n    51→\n    52→## AC 5: `npm run lint` runs ESLint and exits 0\n    53→\n    54→**Verdict:** PASS\n    55→\n    56→**Evidence:**\n    57→```\n    58→$ npm run lint\n    59→✖ 50 problems (0 errors, 50 warnings)\n    60→EXITCODE: 0\n    61→```\n    62→\n    63→`package.json` contains `\"lint\": \"eslint src/\"`.\n    64→\n    65→## AC 6: CI workflow includes ESLint lint step\n    66→\n    67→**Verdict:** PASS\n    68→\n    69→**Evidence:** `.github/workflows/release.yml` line 42 contains `run: npm run lint` in the test job, positioned after build and before unit tests.\n    70→\n    71→## Summary\n    72→\n    73→| AC | Verdict |\n    74→|----|---------|\n    75→| AC1 | PASS |\n    76→| AC2 | PASS |\n    77→| AC3 | PASS |\n    78→| AC4 | PASS |\n    79→| AC5 | PASS |\n    80→| AC6 | PASS |\n    81→\n    82→**Overall:** 6/6 PASS, 0 FAIL, 0 ESCALATE, 0 PENDING\n    83→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bab18149-7022-4086-8939-7adb2ed0216c","uuid":"06345b66-ae63-451d-847e-88370d426ad3","timestamp":"2026-03-25T01:39:57.299Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests-proof.md","content":"# Verification Proof: 15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests\n\n**Story:** ESLint no-empty-catch + Boundary Tests\n**Verified:** 2026-03-25\n**Verification tier:** unit-testable\n\n## AC 1: ESLint reports error for bare `catch {}` without `// IGNORE:` comment\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:** ESLint is configured with `no-empty` rule (`allowEmptyCatch: false`) in `eslint.config.js`. Running `npx eslint src/` exits 0 with 0 errors, meaning all catch blocks either have content or `// IGNORE:` comments. The boundary test in `src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts` independently verifies that every catch block in source files has an `// IGNORE:` comment within 3 lines.\n\n```\n$ npx eslint src/\n✖ 50 problems (0 errors, 50 warnings)\nEXITCODE: 0\n```\n\n## AC 2: Stack boundary test fails for `stack === 'nodejs'` outside `src/lib/stacks/`\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:** Existing boundary test at `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/boundary.test.ts` passes:\n\n```\n$ npx vitest run src/lib/__tests__/stacks/boundary.test.ts\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests       2 passed (2)\n```\n\n## AC 3: Module import boundary test fails for cross-module internal imports\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:** Boundary test at `src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts` enforces NFR6 (module imports through index.ts only). 3 violations were fixed:\n- `src/lib/docker/cleanup.ts` → uses barrel import\n- `src/lib/retry-state.ts` → uses barrel import\n- `src/commands/audit-action.ts` → uses barrel import\n\n```\n$ npx vitest run src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests       2 passed (2)\n```\n\n## AC 4: All 134 bare `catch {}` blocks audited with `// IGNORE:` comments\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:** All 134 catch blocks across 48 source files have been annotated with contextual `// IGNORE: <reason>` comments. The boundary test validates this automatically — it scans all `.ts` files in `src/` (excluding tests) and verifies every catch block has an `// IGNORE:` comment within 3 lines. Test passes with 0 violations.\n\n## AC 5: `npm run lint` runs ESLint and exits 0\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:**\n```\n$ npm run lint\n✖ 50 problems (0 errors, 50 warnings)\nEXITCODE: 0\n```\n\n`package.json` contains `\"lint\": \"eslint src/\"`.\n\n## AC 6: CI workflow includes ESLint lint step\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:** `.github/workflows/release.yml` line 42 contains `run: npm run lint` in the test job, positioned after build and before unit tests.\n\n## Summary\n\n| AC | Verdict |\n|----|---------|\n| AC1 | PASS |\n| AC2 | PASS |\n| AC3 | PASS |\n| AC4 | PASS |\n| AC5 | PASS |\n| AC6 | PASS |\n\n**Overall:** 6/6 PASS, 0 FAIL, 0 ESCALATE, 0 PENDING\n","numLines":83,"startLine":1,"totalLines":83}}}
