{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01USHei1ZmqQyZUEWHq6hqRo","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests-proof.md has been updated. All occurrences were successfully replaced."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bab18149-7022-4086-8939-7adb2ed0216c","uuid":"0d1dacb4-0bd8-443b-9057-b0f10d2078e3","timestamp":"2026-03-25T01:40:03.675Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests-proof.md","oldString":"**Verdict:** PASS","newString":"**Result: PASS**","originalFile":"# Verification Proof: 15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests\n\n**Story:** ESLint no-empty-catch + Boundary Tests\n**Verified:** 2026-03-25\n**Verification tier:** unit-testable\n\n## AC 1: ESLint reports error for bare `catch {}` without `// IGNORE:` comment\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:** ESLint is configured with `no-empty` rule (`allowEmptyCatch: false`) in `eslint.config.js`. Running `npx eslint src/` exits 0 with 0 errors, meaning all catch blocks either have content or `// IGNORE:` comments. The boundary test in `src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts` independently verifies that every catch block in source files has an `// IGNORE:` comment within 3 lines.\n\n```\n$ npx eslint src/\n✖ 50 problems (0 errors, 50 warnings)\nEXITCODE: 0\n```\n\n## AC 2: Stack boundary test fails for `stack === 'nodejs'` outside `src/lib/stacks/`\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:** Existing boundary test at `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/boundary.test.ts` passes:\n\n```\n$ npx vitest run src/lib/__tests__/stacks/boundary.test.ts\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests       2 passed (2)\n```\n\n## AC 3: Module import boundary test fails for cross-module internal imports\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:** Boundary test at `src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts` enforces NFR6 (module imports through index.ts only). 3 violations were fixed:\n- `src/lib/docker/cleanup.ts` → uses barrel import\n- `src/lib/retry-state.ts` → uses barrel import\n- `src/commands/audit-action.ts` → uses barrel import\n\n```\n$ npx vitest run src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests       2 passed (2)\n```\n\n## AC 4: All 134 bare `catch {}` blocks audited with `// IGNORE:` comments\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:** All 134 catch blocks across 48 source files have been annotated with contextual `// IGNORE: <reason>` comments. The boundary test validates this automatically — it scans all `.ts` files in `src/` (excluding tests) and verifies every catch block has an `// IGNORE:` comment within 3 lines. Test passes with 0 violations.\n\n## AC 5: `npm run lint` runs ESLint and exits 0\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:**\n```\n$ npm run lint\n✖ 50 problems (0 errors, 50 warnings)\nEXITCODE: 0\n```\n\n`package.json` contains `\"lint\": \"eslint src/\"`.\n\n## AC 6: CI workflow includes ESLint lint step\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:** `.github/workflows/release.yml` line 42 contains `run: npm run lint` in the test job, positioned after build and before unit tests.\n\n## Summary\n\n| AC | Verdict |\n|----|---------|\n| AC1 | PASS |\n| AC2 | PASS |\n| AC3 | PASS |\n| AC4 | PASS |\n| AC5 | PASS |\n| AC6 | PASS |\n\n**Overall:** 6/6 PASS, 0 FAIL, 0 ESCALATE, 0 PENDING\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":6,"oldLines":7,"newStart":6,"newLines":7,"lines":[" "," ## AC 1: ESLint reports error for bare `catch {}` without `// IGNORE:` comment"," ","-**Verdict:** PASS","+**Result: PASS**"," "," **Evidence:** ESLint is configured with `no-empty` rule (`allowEmptyCatch: false`) in `eslint.config.js`. Running `npx eslint src/` exits 0 with 0 errors, meaning all catch blocks either have content or `// IGNORE:` comments. The boundary test in `src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts` independently verifies that every catch block in source files has an `// IGNORE:` comment within 3 lines."," "]},{"oldStart":18,"oldLines":7,"newStart":18,"newLines":7,"lines":[" "," ## AC 2: Stack boundary test fails for `stack === 'nodejs'` outside `src/lib/stacks/`"," ","-**Verdict:** PASS","+**Result: PASS**"," "," **Evidence:** Existing boundary test at `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/boundary.test.ts` passes:"," "]},{"oldStart":30,"oldLines":7,"newStart":30,"newLines":7,"lines":[" "," ## AC 3: Module import boundary test fails for cross-module internal imports"," ","-**Verdict:** PASS","+**Result: PASS**"," "," **Evidence:** Boundary test at `src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts` enforces NFR6 (module imports through index.ts only). 3 violations were fixed:"," - `src/lib/docker/cleanup.ts` → uses barrel import"]},{"oldStart":45,"oldLines":13,"newStart":45,"newLines":13,"lines":[" "," ## AC 4: All 134 bare `catch {}` blocks audited with `// IGNORE:` comments"," ","-**Verdict:** PASS","+**Result: PASS**"," "," **Evidence:** All 134 catch blocks across 48 source files have been annotated with contextual `// IGNORE: <reason>` comments. The boundary test validates this automatically — it scans all `.ts` files in `src/` (excluding tests) and verifies every catch block has an `// IGNORE:` comment within 3 lines. Test passes with 0 violations."," "," ## AC 5: `npm run lint` runs ESLint and exits 0"," ","-**Verdict:** PASS","+**Result: PASS**"," "," **Evidence:**"," ```"]},{"oldStart":64,"oldLines":7,"newStart":64,"newLines":7,"lines":[" "," ## AC 6: CI workflow includes ESLint lint step"," ","-**Verdict:** PASS","+**Result: PASS**"," "," **Evidence:** `.github/workflows/release.yml` line 42 contains `run: npm run lint` in the test job, positioned after build and before unit tests."," "]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":true}}
