routinely exceed. Followed existing pattern.\n    50→- Observation: docker/cleanup.ts stub tests fully rewritten — implementation changed from no-op to delegation.\n    51→\n    52→### 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup — code-review (2026-03-25T02:52:00Z)\n    53→\n    54→- MEDIUM (fixed): AGENTS.md files for infra and commands modules were stale\n    55→- LOW (unfixed): `isDockerAvailable()` uses `docker --version` not `docker info` — only checks CLI presence, not daemon. Pre-existing across codebase.\n    56→- LOW (unfixed): Double `isDockerAvailable()` call — run.ts checks, then cleanupContainers() checks again. Harmless overhead.\n    57→- Architecture concern: docker --version vs docker info gap means AC#1 may not catch daemon-stopped-but-CLI-installed case. Pre-existing design decision.\n    58→\n    59→### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — create-story (2026-03-25T03:05:00Z)\n    60→\n    61→- Risk: docker-setup.ts at 299 lines — adding backend-aware compose selection will push past 300-line limit\n    62→- Risk: formatters.ts at 574 lines (pre-existing violation) — any additions worsen it\n    63→- Risk: state.ts at 293 lines — adding backend field + migration pushes close to 300\n    64→- Observation: Epic says \"ELK\" but code uses OpenSearchBackend (OpenSearch = OSS Elasticsearch fork). User-facing `--observability-backend elk` maps to internal 'opensearch'. Documented in anti-patterns.\n    65→- Observation: Codebase well-prepared — ObservabilityBackend interface, VictoriaBackend, OpenSearchBackend all exist. Main gap is CLI selector and backend-aware health check dispatch.\n    66→\n    67→### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — dev-story (2026-03-25T03:15:00Z)\n    68→\n    69→- docker-setup.ts at exactly 300 lines — zero margin. Any future change requires extraction.\n    70→- formatters.ts grew from 574 to 597 lines (pre-existing violation, grew by 23 lines). Backend-aware checks in 3 functions each needed guards.\n    71→- Missing getElkComposeFilePath mock caused silent failure in init-project tests — fixed by adding mock and defensive writeState before Docker setup.\n    72→- ELK compose endpoints not backend-specific — DEFAULT_ENDPOINTS still show Victoria ports even for ELK backend. Known gap, not in ACs.\n    73→\n    74→### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — code-review (2026-03-25T03:25:00Z)\n    75→\n    76→- HIGH (fixed): Missing CLI validation for --observability-backend — unsafe `as` cast allows arbitrary strings\n    77→- MEDIUM (fixed): ELK compose file resolution — 4 formatter functions resolved to Victoria compose even for ELK backend\n    78→- MEDIUM (fixed): Wrong endpoints displayed for ELK — Victoria ports shown instead of OpenSearch ports\n    79→- MEDIUM (fixed): resolveEndpoints() not backend-aware — always returned Victoria defaults\n    80→- LOW (unfixed): --no-observability vs --observability-backend none have subtly different semantics\n    81→- LOW (unfixed): formatters.ts at 605 lines — pre-existing violation, now worse\n    82→- LOW (unfixed): docker-setup.ts at exactly 300 lines — fragile\n    83→- Coverage gap: No integration tests for full init --observability-backend elk CLI flow\n    84→- Architecture: buildScopedEndpoints() uses Victoria-specific URL patterns meaningless for ELK\n    85→\n    86→### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — verification-infra (2026-03-25T03:28:00Z)\n    87→\n    88→- Docker daemon unavailable despite Docker Desktop processes running. Socket exists but not responding.\n    89→- Waited 120+ seconds across two attempts. Infra attempt 3/10 (cumulative with prior sessions).\n    90→- Story skipped — cannot run black-box verification without Docker.\n    91→\n    92→### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — create-story (2026-03-25T03:32:00Z)\n    93→\n    94→- Observation: env.ts already over 300-line limit at 313 lines (pre-existing violation). Story guides extraction to dockerfile-generator.ts.\n    95→- Observation: nodejs.ts at 346 lines — also over 300-line limit. Adding getVerifyDockerfileSection() will increase it further.\n    96→- Risk: Static template deprecation — generated approach replaces them entirely. If external consumers reference templates directly, they'll break silently.\n    97→- Ambiguity: Ubuntu 22.04 vs stack-specific base images. Architecture specifies ubuntu:22.04 but current templates use node:20-slim and rust:1.82-slim. Switching increases build time.\n    98→\n    99→### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — dev-story (2026-03-25T03:41:00Z)\n   100→\n   101→- env.ts still at 304 lines — down from 313 but still over the 300-line NFR1 limit by 4 lines. Further extraction out of scope.\n   102→- Static templates not deleted — kept deprecated for backward compat with older installed versions. Now dead code from main build path.\n   103→- NodejsProvider at 358 lines — exceeds 300-line NFR1. Was 346 pre-story, added 12 lines. Pre-existing tech debt.\n   104→\n   105→### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — verification-infra (2026-03-25T03:50:00Z)\n   106→\n   107→- Docker daemon not running — socket not responding. Cannot start observability stack.\n   108→- Retry count incremented from 3 to 4. Story remains at verifying.\n   109→- Same infrastructure issue as prior session — Docker Desktop needs to be started manually on macOS.\n   110→\n   111→### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — verification-infra (2026-03-25T03:50:00Z)\n   112→\n   113→- Docker daemon not running — same issue as 14-4. Cannot perform black-box verification.\n   114→- Retry count corrected: 14-5 was actually at `backlog` in sprint-state.json (yaml was stale). Reset to 0.\n   115→\n   116→### 14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget — create-story (2026-03-25T03:52:00Z)\n   117→\n   118→- Expanded from 2 to 10 ACs covering status ownership, time budget logic, prompt cleanup, build/test gates\n   119→- Risk: AC6 (remove state-writing from prompts) depends on finding all prompt instructions — may miss indirect ones\n   120→- Risk: Session budget plumbing from ralph to TS orchestrator not fully specified\n   121→- Data inconsistency found: sprint-state.json had 14-5 as `backlog` but yaml had `verifying`. Fixed both to `verifying`.\n   122→\n   123→### 14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget — dev-story (2026-03-25T04:00:00Z)\n   124→\n   125→- Architectural mismatch: run.ts spawns a single long-running ralph process. Time budget deferral logs warnings but cannot actually kill/pause the subagent mid-phase. True phase-level control would need ralph to expose phase-change events.\n   126→- Status ownership simplification: `story-complete` event always writes `in-review`. A phase-aware mapping would be more correct but requires knowing what phase fired the event (not in the event payload).\n   127→- All 3729 vitest tests + 307 BATS tests pass. Build succeeds.\n   128→\n   129→### 14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget — code-review (2026-03-25T04:10:00Z)\n   130→\n   131→- HIGH (fixed): Time budget deferral was fire-and-forget — logged but never killed the agent process. Now calls child.kill('SIGTERM').\n   132→- HIGH (fixed): updateStoryStatus() return value silently discarded. Now logs warnings on failure.\n   133→- MEDIUM (fixed): shouldDeferPhase returned false for NaN input (don't defer when budget unknown). Now returns true (safe default).\n   134→- LOW (unfixed): warn import inconsistency — warnings emitted via info() with [WARN] prefix instead of using warn() helper.\n   135→- Coverage gap: No integration test for full deferral flow (polling -> deferral -> child.kill -> clean exit).\n   136→- Architecture: child.kill('SIGTERM') is abrupt — no graceful shutdown protocol for subagent to save progress.\n   137→- Architecture: 5-second polling interval means up to 5s window where phase could start before deferral.\n   138→- All 3733 tests pass. 96.97% overall coverage. All 156 files above 80% floor.\n   139→\n   140→### 14-4/14-5/14-6 — verification-infra (2026-03-25T00: